  "Question": "<p>The proof is required to be made through the binomial theorem. I will expose the demonstration I was tought, and forward my questions after exposing it. You'll see question marks like this one <strong>(?-n)</strong> on points I don't quite understand, where <span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_662\"><?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?> <math alttext=\"n\" display=\"block\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"> <mi>n</mi> </math></span> is the numeration of the mark. This are the doubts I have about the demonstration, the which I hope someone can clarify.</p> <p>Prove that <span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_663\"><?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?> <math alttext=\"\\binom{n}{0}^{2}+\\binom{n}{1}^{2}+...+\\binom{n}{n}^{2}=\\binom{2n}{n}\" display=\"block\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"> <mrow> <mrow> <mrow> <merror class=\"ltx_ERROR undefined undefined\"> <mtext>\\binom</mtext> </merror> <mo>\u2062</mo> <mi>n</mi> <mo>\u2062</mo> <msup> <mn>0</mn> <mn>2</mn> </msup> </mrow> <mo>+</mo> <mrow> <merror class=\"ltx_ERROR undefined undefined\"> <mtext>\\binom</mtext> </merror> <mo>\u2062</mo> <mi>n</mi> <mo>\u2062</mo> <msup> <mn>1</mn> <mn>2</mn> </msup> </mrow> <mo>+</mo> <mi mathvariant=\"normal\">\u2026</mi> <mo>+</mo> <mrow> <merror class=\"ltx_ERROR undefined undefined\"> <mtext>\\binom</mtext> </merror> <mo>\u2062</mo> <mi>n</mi> <mo>\u2062</mo> <msup> <mi>n</mi> <mn>2</mn> </msup> </mrow> </mrow> <mo>=</mo> <mrow> <merror class=\"ltx_ERROR undefined undefined\"> <mtext>\\binom</mtext> </merror> <mo>\u2062</mo> <mn>2</mn> <mo>\u2062</mo> <mi>n</mi> <mo>\u2062</mo> <mi>n</mi> </mrow> </mrow> </math></span>.</p> <p>We will use the following equality, and call it <span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_664\"><?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?> <math alttext=\"P\" display=\"block\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"> <mi>P</mi> </math></span>: </p> <p><span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_665\"><?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?> <math alttext=\"(1+x)^{n}(1+x)^{n}=(1+x)^{2n}\" display=\"block\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"> <mrow> <mrow> <msup> <mrow> <mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo> <mrow> <mn>1</mn> <mo>+</mo> <mi>x</mi> </mrow> <mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo> </mrow> <mi>n</mi> </msup> <mo>\u2062</mo> <msup> <mrow> <mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo> <mrow> <mn>1</mn> <mo>+</mo> <mi>x</mi> </mrow> <mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo> </mrow> <mi>n</mi> </msup> </mrow> <mo>=</mo> <msup> <mrow> <mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo> <mrow> <mn>1</mn> <mo>+</mo> <mi>x</mi> </mrow> <mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo> </mrow> <mrow> <mn>2</mn> <mo>\u2062</mo> <mi>n</mi> </mrow> </msup> </mrow> </math></span> <strong>(?-1)</strong></p> <p>The result will be proved finding the <span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_666\"><?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?> <math alttext=\"x^{n}\" display=\"block\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"> <msup> <mi>x</mi> <mi>n</mi> </msup> </math></span> coefficient of both terms of this equality <strong>(?-2)</strong>.</p> <p>According to the binomial theorem, the left-hand side of this equation is the product of two factors, both equal to</p> <p><span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_667\"><?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?> <math alttext=\"\\binom{n}{0}1+\\binom{n}{1}x+...+\\binom{n}{r}x^{r}+...+\\binom{n}{n}x^{n}\" display=\"block\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"> <mrow> <mrow> <merror class=\"ltx_ERROR undefined undefined\"> <mtext>\\binom</mtext> </merror> <mo>\u2062</mo> <mi>n</mi> <mo>\u2062</mo> <mn>01</mn> </mrow> <mo>+</mo> <mrow> <merror class=\"ltx_ERROR undefined undefined\"> <mtext>\\binom</mtext> </merror> <mo>\u2062</mo> <mi>n</mi> <mo>\u2062</mo> <mn>1</mn> <mo>\u2062</mo> <mi>x</mi> </mrow> <mo>+</mo> <mi mathvariant=\"normal\">\u2026</mi> <mo>+</mo> <mrow> <merror class=\"ltx_ERROR undefined undefined\"> <mtext>\\binom</mtext> </merror> <mo>\u2062</mo> <mi>n</mi> <mo>\u2062</mo> <mi>r</mi> <mo>\u2062</mo> <msup> <mi>x</mi> <mi>r</mi> </msup> </mrow> <mo>+</mo> <mi mathvariant=\"normal\">\u2026</mi> <mo>+</mo> <mrow> <merror class=\"ltx_ERROR undefined undefined\"> <mtext>\\binom</mtext> </merror> <mo>\u2062</mo> <mi>n</mi> <mo>\u2062</mo> <mi>n</mi> <mo>\u2062</mo> <msup> <mi>x</mi> <mi>n</mi> </msup> </mrow> </mrow> </math></span></p> <p>When both factors multiply, a term on <span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_668\"><?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?> <math alttext=\"x^{n}\" display=\"block\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"> <msup> <mi>x</mi> <mi>n</mi> </msup> </math></span> is obtained when a term of the first factor has some <span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_669\"><?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?> <math alttext=\"x^{i}\" display=\"block\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"> <msup> <mi>x</mi> <mi>i</mi> </msup> </math></span> and the term of the second factor has some <span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_670\"><?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?> <math alttext=\"x^{n-i}\" display=\"block\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"> <msup> <mi>x</mi> <mrow> <mi>n</mi> <mo>-</mo> <mi>i</mi> </mrow> </msup> </math></span>. Therefor the coefficients of <span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_671\"><?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?> <math alttext=\"x^{n}\" display=\"block\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"> <msup> <mi>x</mi> <mi>n</mi> </msup> </math></span> are</p> <p><span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_672\"><?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?> <math alttext=\"\\binom{n}{0}\\binom{n}{n}+\\binom{n}{1}\\binom{n}{n-1}+\\binom{n}{2}\\binom{n}{n-2}%\n+...\\binom{n}{n}\\binom{n}{0}\" display=\"block\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"> <mrow> <mrow> <mrow> <mrow> <mrow> <mrow> <merror class=\"ltx_ERROR undefined undefined\"> <mtext>\\binom</mtext> </merror> <mo>\u2062</mo> <mi>n</mi> <mo>\u2062</mo> <mn>0</mn> <mo>\u2062</mo> <merror class=\"ltx_ERROR undefined undefined\"> <mtext>\\binom</mtext> </merror> <mo>\u2062</mo> <mi>n</mi> <mo>\u2062</mo> <mi>n</mi> </mrow> <mo>+</mo> <mrow> <merror class=\"ltx_ERROR undefined undefined\"> <mtext>\\binom</mtext> </merror> <mo>\u2062</mo> <mi>n</mi> <mo>\u2062</mo> <mn>1</mn> <mo>\u2062</mo> <merror class=\"ltx_ERROR undefined undefined\"> <mtext>\\binom</mtext> </merror> <mo>\u2062</mo> <mi>n</mi> <mo>\u2062</mo> <mi>n</mi> </mrow> </mrow> <mo>-</mo> <mn>1</mn> </mrow> <mo>+</mo> <mrow> <merror class=\"ltx_ERROR undefined undefined\"> <mtext>\\binom</mtext> </merror> <mo>\u2062</mo> <mi>n</mi> <mo>\u2062</mo> <mn>2</mn> <mo>\u2062</mo> <merror class=\"ltx_ERROR undefined undefined\"> <mtext>\\binom</mtext> </merror> <mo>\u2062</mo> <mi>n</mi> <mo>\u2062</mo> <mi>n</mi> </mrow> </mrow> <mo>-</mo> <mn>2</mn> </mrow> <mo>+</mo> <mrow> <mi mathvariant=\"normal\">\u2026</mi> <mo>\u2062</mo> <merror class=\"ltx_ERROR undefined undefined\"> <mtext>\\binom</mtext> </merror> <mo>\u2062</mo> <mi>n</mi> <mo>\u2062</mo> <mi>n</mi> <mo>\u2062</mo> <merror class=\"ltx_ERROR undefined undefined\"> <mtext>\\binom</mtext> </merror> <mo>\u2062</mo> <mi>n</mi> <mo>\u2062</mo> <mn>0</mn> </mrow> </mrow> </math></span> .</p> <p>Since <span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_673\"><?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?> <math alttext=\"\\binom{n}{n-r}=\\binom{n}{r}\" display=\"block\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"> <mrow> <mrow> <mrow> <merror class=\"ltx_ERROR undefined undefined\"> <mtext>\\binom</mtext> </merror> <mo>\u2062</mo> <mi>n</mi> <mo>\u2062</mo> <mi>n</mi> </mrow> <mo>-</mo> <mi>r</mi> </mrow> <mo>=</mo> <mrow> <merror class=\"ltx_ERROR undefined undefined\"> <mtext>\\binom</mtext> </merror> <mo>\u2062</mo> <mi>n</mi> <mo>\u2062</mo> <mi>r</mi> </mrow> </mrow> </math></span>, the previous summation is equal to <span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_674\"><?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?> <math alttext=\"\\binom{n}{0}^{2}+\\binom{n}{1}^{2}+...+\\binom{n}{n}^{2}\" display=\"block\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"> <mrow> <mrow> <merror class=\"ltx_ERROR undefined undefined\"> <mtext>\\binom</mtext> </merror> <mo>\u2062</mo> <mi>n</mi> <mo>\u2062</mo> <msup> <mn>0</mn> <mn>2</mn> </msup> </mrow> <mo>+</mo> <mrow> <merror class=\"ltx_ERROR undefined undefined\"> <mtext>\\binom</mtext> </merror> <mo>\u2062</mo> <mi>n</mi> <mo>\u2062</mo> <msup> <mn>1</mn> <mn>2</mn> </msup> </mrow> <mo>+</mo> <mi mathvariant=\"normal\">\u2026</mi> <mo>+</mo> <mrow> <merror class=\"ltx_ERROR undefined undefined\"> <mtext>\\binom</mtext> </merror> <mo>\u2062</mo> <mi>n</mi> <mo>\u2062</mo> <msup> <mi>n</mi> <mn>2</mn> </msup> </mrow> </mrow> </math></span>. So the left hand side of the equation we are asked to proove is a coefficient of <span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_675\"><?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?> <math alttext=\"x^{n}\" display=\"block\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"> <msup> <mi>x</mi> <mi>n</mi> </msup> </math></span>. When we expand the right-hand side of the equation <span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_676\"><?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?> <math alttext=\"P\" display=\"block\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"> <mi>P</mi> </math></span>, we find that <span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_677\"><?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?> <math alttext=\"\\binom{2n}{n}\" display=\"block\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"> <mrow> <merror class=\"ltx_ERROR undefined undefined\"> <mtext>\\binom</mtext> </merror> <mo>\u2062</mo> <mn>2</mn> <mo>\u2062</mo> <mi>n</mi> <mo>\u2062</mo> <mi>n</mi> </mrow> </math></span> is a coefficient of <span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_678\"><?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?> <math alttext=\"x^{n}\" display=\"block\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"> <msup> <mi>x</mi> <mi>n</mi> </msup> </math></span>. Therefore <strong>(?-3)</strong> the left-hand side of the equation we were asked to prove is in deed equal to <span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_679\"><?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?> <math alttext=\"\\binom{2n}{n}\" display=\"block\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"> <mrow> <merror class=\"ltx_ERROR undefined undefined\"> <mtext>\\binom</mtext> </merror> <mo>\u2062</mo> <mn>2</mn> <mo>\u2062</mo> <mi>n</mi> <mo>\u2062</mo> <mi>n</mi> </mrow> </math></span>. In conclussion,</p> <p><span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_680\"><?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?> <math alttext=\"\\binom{n}{0}^{2}+\\binom{n}{1}^{2}+...+\\binom{n}{n}^{2}=\\binom{2n}{n}\" display=\"block\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"> <mrow> <mrow> <mrow> <merror class=\"ltx_ERROR undefined undefined\"> <mtext>\\binom</mtext> </merror> <mo>\u2062</mo> <mi>n</mi> <mo>\u2062</mo> <msup> <mn>0</mn> <mn>2</mn> </msup> </mrow> <mo>+</mo> <mrow> <merror class=\"ltx_ERROR undefined undefined\"> <mtext>\\binom</mtext> </merror> <mo>\u2062</mo> <mi>n</mi> <mo>\u2062</mo> <msup> <mn>1</mn> <mn>2</mn> </msup> </mrow> <mo>+</mo> <mi mathvariant=\"normal\">\u2026</mi> <mo>+</mo> <mrow> <merror class=\"ltx_ERROR undefined undefined\"> <mtext>\\binom</mtext> </merror> <mo>\u2062</mo> <mi>n</mi> <mo>\u2062</mo> <msup> <mi>n</mi> <mn>2</mn> </msup> </mrow> </mrow> <mo>=</mo> <mrow> <merror class=\"ltx_ERROR undefined undefined\"> <mtext>\\binom</mtext> </merror> <mo>\u2062</mo> <mn>2</mn> <mo>\u2062</mo> <mi>n</mi> <mo>\u2062</mo> <mi>n</mi> </mrow> </mrow> </math></span>.</p> <p>This was all the demonstration. My doubt one <strong>(?-1)</strong> goes about where the heck does this equation come from? How would I know what equation to come up with if requested to prove a different equality?</p> <p>Doubt two <strong>(?-2)</strong> goes about why would the solution of the first equation would have anything to do with finding the <span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_681\"><?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?> <math alttext=\"x^{n}\" display=\"block\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"> <msup> <mi>x</mi> <mi>n</mi> </msup> </math></span> coefficients of the one I just made up (see doubt one).</p> <p>Doubt three <strong>(?-3)</strong> goes about why demonstrating that <span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_682\"><?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?> <math alttext=\"a\" display=\"block\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"> <mi>a</mi> </math></span> is a coefficient of <span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_683\"><?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?> <math alttext=\"x^{n}\" display=\"block\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"> <msup> <mi>x</mi> <mi>n</mi> </msup> </math></span> on the left hand side of the equation I made up, and that <span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_684\"><?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?> <math alttext=\"b\" display=\"block\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"> <mi>b</mi> </math></span> is a coefficient of <span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_685\"><?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?> <math alttext=\"x^{n}\" display=\"block\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"> <msup> <mi>x</mi> <mi>n</mi> </msup> </math></span> on the right-hand side of this equation as well, would prove my original equation, the one I was supposed to prove on the first place?</p> <p>I know there are many doubts here, I hope you guys can help me. Sorry for the long post, it's a long demonstration.</p>",
  "Title": "Help on proof of <span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_661\"><?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?> <math alttext=\"\\binom{n}{0}^{2}+\\binom{n}{1}^{2}+...+\\binom{n}{n}^{2}=\\binom{2n}{n}\" display=\"block\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"> <mrow> <mrow> <mrow> <merror class=\"ltx_ERROR undefined undefined\"> <mtext>\\binom</mtext> </merror> <mo>\u2062</mo> <mi>n</mi> <mo>\u2062</mo> <msup> <mn>0</mn> <mn>2</mn> </msup> </mrow> <mo>+</mo> <mrow> <merror class=\"ltx_ERROR undefined undefined\"> <mtext>\\binom</mtext> </merror> <mo>\u2062</mo> <mi>n</mi> <mo>\u2062</mo> <msup> <mn>1</mn> <mn>2</mn> </msup> </mrow> <mo>+</mo> <mi mathvariant=\"normal\">\u2026</mi> <mo>+</mo> <mrow> <merror class=\"ltx_ERROR undefined undefined\"> <mtext>\\binom</mtext> </merror> <mo>\u2062</mo> <mi>n</mi> <mo>\u2062</mo> <msup> <mi>n</mi> <mn>2</mn> </msup> </mrow> </mrow> <mo>=</mo> <mrow> <merror class=\"ltx_ERROR undefined undefined\"> <mtext>\\binom</mtext> </merror> <mo>\u2062</mo> <mn>2</mn> <mo>\u2062</mo> <mi>n</mi> <mo>\u2062</mo> <mi>n</mi> </mrow> </mrow> </math></span>",
